item_description: Resuscitation of a patient provided for at least 1 hour but less than 2 hours, by a specialist in the practice of the specialistâ€™s specialty of emergency medicine at a recognised emergency department of a private hospital, in conjunction with an attendance on the patient by the specialist described in item 5001, 5004, 5011, 5012, 5013, 5014, 5016, 5017 or 5019 (Anaes.)
rationale: The note describes a patient with a bicycle accident and concussion, managed with reassurance and education, with no mention of resuscitation or emergency intervention. There is no evidence of a resuscitation event lasting at least 60 minutes.
citations: Patient 11 years old with history of bicycle accident involving head and leg impact, with brief loss of consciousness.
Management: Reassurance, education on short-term and long-term effects of concussion; advice to return to ED if concerns arise in next 24-48 hours.
